Alternatively, according to some records, the name ILUKO is derived from l- (originating from) and LUKU or LUKUNG (a valley or depression of land, hence "lowland"). It is located between the GULOD (mountains) and the LUEK (sea) (bay). IlocANO is the Spanish word for "us" ANO, which refers to the people (e.g., AmericANO, AfricANO, MexicANO, etc.).
